VekBase/
├─ app/
│  ├─ analytics/        # metrics.py (REALIZED Metrics + unrealized overlay helper), patterns.py (Histogram/Scatter Implementierung + UI Flag VEK_PATTERNS)
│  ├─ core/             # trade_model, trade_repo, retrieval (Keyword Stub + ticker/as_of Filter), decision_card, (Simulation uses sim/)
│  ├─ sim/              # simple_walk (deterministische Mini-Simulation + Persistenz)
│  └─ ui/               # console.py (Streamlit Konsole: Trades, Analytics, Simulation, DevTools)
│  (NEW) core/devtools.py    # Test Discovery & Runner Abstraktion (UI nutzt öffentliche Funktionen)
│  (NEW) core/linttools.py   # Lightweight Lint (Syntax, Whitespace, Mixed Indent) ohne externe Abhängigkeiten
│  (NEW) core/benchtools.py  # Einfache Benchmark Harness (Median ms + Baseline Persistenz) für ausgewählte Analytics
│  (NEW) core/snapshots.py   # Snapshot Regression Harness (metrics & equity_curve) + Diff + Baseline Update
│  (NEW) core/decision_card_repo.py # JSON Persistenz für DecisionCards (data/decision_cards.json)
│  (NEW) core/testqueue.py   # Parallele/ persistente Testqueue (JSONL + Output Files, Retry, Truncation)
├─ data/                # (lokal, nicht versioniert erwartet) trades.csv, results/, optional notes/, cache/
├─ docs/
│  ├─ CONTEXT/          # 10 Kontext-Dateien (Charter, Manifesto, Glossary, Schema, Decision Spec, RAG Policy, Test Strategy, UI Spec, Roadmap, Working Agreements)
│  └─ DOCUMENTATION/    # architecture, tmp_backlogCollection (Backlog Sammelstelle)
├─ tests/               # Pytest Module (trade_model, metrics, retrieval, sim, equity curve, etc.)
├─ README.md            # Kurzstart (lokal-first)
└─ requirements.txt     # Python Abhängigkeiten (leichtgewichtig)

Not Implemented / PARTIAL (Backlog Referenz):
- Retrieval Filter & Snippet Qualität (ticker/as_of) (P1)
- Erweiterte Sim Parameter (TP/SL/Kosten) (P1)
- Unrealized Equity Curve Erweiterung (P1)
- Erweiterte Pattern Analytics (PARTIAL – Basis implementiert) (P2)
- Snapshot Regression Coverage Ausbau (P2)
- Queue Aggregate Metrics & Retention Policy (P2)
- Live Quotes Cache (optional P3)
- Optionale Embeddings/RAG Ranking (Deferred)

Konventionen:
- Keine sys.path Hacks (Packaging + pytest config)
- Reine Berechnungen in analytics; Persistenz explizit in sim/simple_walk.run_and_persist & devtools (snapshots/benchmarks/testqueue) unter `data/devtools/`
- Queue Persistenz auditierbar (append-only JSONL + getrennte Output Artefakte)
- Kontext-Sync: Roadmap & Backlog (single source), andere Dateien referenzieren IDs nur summarisch
